INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city New York, in relation to requiring the department of environmental protection to notify water customers who ware owners of class 2 properties, by mail, of large charges that could indicate a potential leak.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of environmental protection to notify water customers who ware owners of class 2 properties, by mail, of large charges that could indicate a potential leak.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting employment discrimination based on an individual’s actual or perceived status as a caregiver.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting employment discrimination based on an individual’s actual or perceived status as a caregiver.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to special parking for accessible for-hire vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Special parking for accessible for-hire vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States House of Representatives and the United States Senate to pass and for the President to reauthorize an adequately funded  Farm Bill that creates a strong and healthy food system.
EventItemMatterName: Reauthorize an adequately funded  Farm Bill that creates a strong and healthy food system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign into law legislation that would amend the State Election Law to modernize and streamline the procedures for the election night canvass and the reporting of unofficial election results.
EventItemMatterName: Modernize and streamline the procedures for the election night canvass and the reporting of unofficial election results.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the New York city building code, in relation to requiring photoelectric smoke detectors in residential buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring photoelectric smoke detectors in residential buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the U.S. government to provide a remedy to the Guatemalan victims of medical experimentation conducted by the U.S. Public Health Service from 1946 to 1953.
EventItemMatterName: Provide a remedy to the Guatemalan victims of medical experimentation conducted by the U.S. Public Health Service from 1946 to 1953.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for the creation of veterans treatment courts in every county in New York City, including the counties of the Bronx, New York and Richmond, to serve and address the increasing needs of the growing veteran population in the City.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of veterans treatment courts in every county in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to enact A. 9804/S.7212, also known as the “Trafficking Victims Protection and Justice Act.”
EventItemMatterName: Trafficking Victims Protection and Justice Act. (A. 9804/S.7212)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting data related to sexually exploited children.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting data related to sexually exploited children.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Gianaris, S.2513, and Assembly Member Simotas, A.4874, “AN ACT to authorize the city of New York to discontinue use of and convey certain park land”.
EventItemMatterName: Discontinue use of and convey certain park land. (S.2513/A.4874)

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Golden, S.6436, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.9367-A, “AN ACT to amend the general municipal law, in relation to training of fire officers in cities of one million or more".
EventItemMatterName: Training of fire officers in cities of one million or more. (S.6436/A.9367-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of a voluntary master environmental hazard remediation technician registration program.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a voluntary master environmental hazard remediation technician registration program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to parking meter suspension.
EventItemMatterName: Parking meter suspension.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.6294-A/A.9084-A, legislation that would prohibit public funding to facilities providing aversive interventions, including but not limited to electric shock therapy, and would remove such facilities from any registry of approved schools.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit public funding to facilities providing aversive interventions, including but not limited to electric shock therapy, and would remove such facilities from any registry of approved schools. (S.6294-A/A.9084-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring all persons to wear a helmet while operating a bicycle.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all persons to wear a helmet while operating a bicycle.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign into law the Weekend Voting Act, which would move federal congressional and presidential elections from Tuesdays to Saturday and Sunday.
EventItemMatterName: Weekend Voting Act

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the New York Dream Act (A. 6829-C/S. 4179-C) to provide benefits to any children of a professional immigrant recruited to serve the United States through public service at the local, state, or federal level, regardless of their age at the time of arrival or at the time of application for benefits.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the New York Dream Act (A. 6829-C/S. 4179-C)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of S.2051/H.R.3826, the Student Loan Affordability Act, which would prevent the current student loan interest rate of 3.4 percent from doubling to 6.8 percent on July 1, 2012.
EventItemMatterName: Would prevent the current student loan interest rate of 3.4 percent from doubling to 6.8 percent on July 1, 2012. (S.2051/H.R.3826)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass A.9869 and S.6868, which directs the State to reimburse the City of New York for the health insurance and supplemental benefits of New York City Off-Track Betting Corporation retirees.
EventItemMatterName: Health insurance and supplemental benefits of NYC Off-Track Betting Corporation retirees. (A.9869/S.6868)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon employers in New York City to hire more workers over 55 years of age.
EventItemMatterName: Employers in NYC to hire more workers over 55 years of age.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to making police data machine-readable.
EventItemMatterName: Making police data machine-readable.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the State Education Law, to change from mayoral control to municipal control of the New York City public school system.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the State Education Law, to change from mayoral control to municipal control of the NYC public school system.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the consumption of alcoholic beverages by minors at private residences.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the consumption of alcoholic beverages by minors at private residences.
